# Create System Architecture (Project Overlay)

The full skill — topology, resilience patterns, contract-first APIs, polyglot persistence, expand/contract migrations — is in the `praxis` plugin's `design-system-architecture` skill. Read it first.

## When to invoke

Pair this with the wave's `product-architecture.md` (see `.github/skills/create-product-architecture-spec/SKILL.md`) when the wave introduces:

- A new external integration (third-party API, identity provider, payment processor)
- A new runtime or deployment surface (worker, scheduled job, event consumer)
- A new trust boundary (B2B tenant, partner API, public webhook)
- A platform-wide constraint (data residency, encryption, retention)

## Project-specific paths

- Output location: a new ADR under `{{paths.adr}}/` capturing the durable system decisions.
- Existing system docs to read first: `{{paths.engineering}}/handbook.md`.
- Active deployment topology: {{stack.deployment_target}}.

## Hand-off

The system architecture decisions must be recorded as one or more ADRs (use `.github/skills/create-adr/SKILL.md`). The wave's `product-architecture.md` then references those ADRs rather than restating the decisions inline.
